30004808@@@@@@Side-view Camera@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1374@LMC@2019-06-14
30004809@@@@@@Background:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1377@LMC@2019-06-14
30004810@@@@@@To have the right to drive, an individual would need to go through a series of theory and practical tests.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1378@LMC@2019-06-14
30004811@@@@@@These tests deem if a driver is fit to drive as well as teach him the rules and regulations of the roads.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1379@LMC@2019-06-14
30004812@@@@@@This ensures that the roads are safe.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1380@LMC@2019-06-14
30004813@@@@@@Problem:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1381@LMC@2019-06-14
30004814@@@@@@Although a driver has sufficient knowledge of the roads, there is an unavoidable issue of blind spots when the driver would like to turn or change lanes.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1382@LMC@2019-06-14
30004815@@@@@@While how to minimise this problem is taught, it still remains a huge accident causing factor on the roads.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1383@LMC@2019-06-14
30004816@@@@@@According to an article by The Telegraph, the number of crashes caused by blind spots has risen by 50% over the last two years.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1384@LMC@2019-06-14
30004817@@@@@@It is found that this could be due to vehicles having strengthened frames which in turns widens the blind spots and affect the view of other cars on the road.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1385@LMC@2019-06-14
30004818@@@@@@There are methods such as sensors that detect movement and flashes a light to the driver, but it may not be effective as by the time the light comes on, it may already be too late.@@@@1@36@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1386@LMC@2019-06-14
30004819@@@@@@Solution:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1387@LMC@2019-06-14
30004820@@@@@@The main objective is to give the driver ‘eyes’ that serve to see where they are unable to.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1388@LMC@2019-06-14
30004821@@@@@@It is an extension of the rear-view camera technology that assist drivers with parking.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1389@LMC@2019-06-14
30004822@@@@@@Cameras will be placed at the side of the vehicle and show the blind spots.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1390@LMC@2019-06-14
30004823@@@@@@This can be built into the vehicle or installed as an external component.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1391@LMC@2019-06-14
30004824@@@@@@When the driver wants to make a turn or a change of lane, upon activation of the turn signal, the camera would switch on and show the blind spot on the screen at the dashboard of the car.@@@@1@38@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1392@LMC@2019-06-14
30004825@@@@@@This ensures that he will always be in view of his blind spot and unnecessary accidents can be avoided.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1393@LMC@2019-06-14
30004826@@@@@@Benefits:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1394@LMC@2019-06-14
30004827@@@@@@This will result in a wider range of vision and effectively ensures that a driver has no one in his blind spots before a turn or a change of lane is made.@@@@1@32@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1395@LMC@2019-06-14
30004828@@@@@@As activation of the turn signal is needed to activate the camera, this also warns other road users of the driver’s intentions.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1396@LMC@2019-06-14
30004829@@@@@@Although this is already a necessary safety precaution, according to a study by the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE), up to 50% of drivers do not signal before they turn.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1397@LMC@2019-06-14
30004830@@@@@@The device will inculcate this good habit on drivers.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1398@LMC@2019-06-14
30004831@@@@@@Implementation:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1399@LMC@2019-06-14
30004832@@@@@@To develop this device, the following steps will be taken:@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1400@LMC@2019-06-14
30004833@@@@@@1@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:167; ntucle-sid:1401@LMC@2019-06-14
