30004875@@@@@@The Smart Library System@@@@1@4@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1249@LMC@2019-06-14
30004876@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1250@LMC@2019-06-14
30004877@@@@@@Libraries play an important role in universities partly because they provide essential study spaces.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1251@LMC@2019-06-14
30004878@@@@@@However, seat-hogging is a prevailing phenomenon which undermines university libraries’ functions.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1252@LMC@2019-06-14
30004879@@@@@@A survey done by Singapore Management University in 2015 revealed that seat-hogging was a major problem in its libraries [1]; surveys conducted in three overseas universities indicated that the majority of students were in favour of actions to be taken against seat-hogging [2] [3] [4].@@@@1@45@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1253@LMC@2019-06-14
30004880@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1254@LMC@2019-06-14
30004881@@@@@@Seat-hogging causes inefficiency and inconvenience in university libraries.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1255@LMC@2019-06-14
30004882@@@@@@Library-goers are often unable to find vacant seats even when the occupiers (“seat-hoggers”) are not actually using them.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1256@LMC@2019-06-14
30004883@@@@@@As a result, the facilities are not used to their full extent to meet students’ needs for study spaces.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1257@LMC@2019-06-14
30004884@@@@@@Moreover, seat-hogging creates extra burden on the librarians because they have to frequently patrol around to ensure the seats are used properly.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1258@LMC@2019-06-14
30004885@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1259@LMC@2019-06-14
30004886@@@@@@The Smart Library System is designed to detect, identify and blacklist seat-hoggers automatically.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1260@LMC@2019-06-14
30004887@@@@@@The system includes card readers installed on tables and low-cost weight sensors inserted under seat cushions.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1261@LMC@2019-06-14
30004888@@@@@@All card readers and weight sensors are connected to the central monitoring unit located at the librarians’ office.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1262@LMC@2019-06-14
30004889@@@@@@User will be required to tap their matric cards on the “card-tapping area” before and after using the seats.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1263@LMC@2019-06-14
30004890@@@@@@The weight sensor will detect the presence of the user on the chair.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:171; ntucle-sid:1264@LMC@2019-06-14
