30005026@@@@@@School of Chemical and Biomedical Engineering@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1222@LMC@2019-06-14
30005027@@@@@@Title : Sensor device to detect unattended stove.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1223@LMC@2019-06-14
30005028@@@@@@There are gas and electric stoves in existence.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1227@LMC@2019-06-14
30005029@@@@@@Electric stoves are generally more expensive thus gas stoves are commonly used across many households.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1228@LMC@2019-06-14
30005030@@@@@@A knob is turned which will put out the fire and stop the flow of gas through the pipes.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1229@LMC@2019-06-14
30005031@@@@@@However, there are some cases whereby the gas leaks.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1230@LMC@2019-06-14
30005032@@@@@@Users will overlook this, as when there is no visible fire seen, they will assume that the stove is switched off.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1231@LMC@2019-06-14
30005033@@@@@@Unattended stoves or those that are not switched off properly are listed in SCDF’s Fire Safety Advisory.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1232@LMC@2019-06-14
30005034@@@@@@There were cases whereby the leakage of gas caused fire to break through.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1233@LMC@2019-06-14
30005035@@@@@@As mentioned, unattended stoves are one of the causes of fire breakouts.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1234@LMC@2019-06-14
30005036@@@@@@The main problem is that there is gas leaking even though the knob is switched off.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1235@LMC@2019-06-14
30005037@@@@@@The solution to overcome the problem is to develop a device that will detect the gas carbon monoxide (CO) emitted after the user attempts to switch the stove off and will automatically close the gas valve in the case where it was not closed.@@@@1@44@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1236@LMC@2019-06-14
30005038@@@@@@When the knob is turned, to put out the fire and the gas, the sensor will be switched on and proceeds to detect the amount of gas emitted.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1237@LMC@2019-06-14
30005039@@@@@@If the gas percentage reaches a limit, the user will be alerted by a beep sound.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1238@LMC@2019-06-14
30005040@@@@@@If the sensor is not attended within 40 seconds, the pipes where the gas flows will be blocked.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1239@LMC@2019-06-14
30005041@@@@@@The device will be automatically switched off when no gas is detected in a few minutes.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1240@LMC@2019-06-14
30005042@@@@@@Several components are needed before this device can be developed.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1241@LMC@2019-06-14
30005043@@@@@@They include the microprocessor, sensor, LCD display, buzzer, switches, battery contact and circuit board.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1242@LMC@2019-06-14
30005044@@@@@@The sensor used has to be capable of detecting the percentage of CO emitted.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1243@LMC@2019-06-14
30005045@@@@@@The microprocessor has to be programmed to send information to the LCD display, trigger the buzzer and the switch (that will block the gas flow) when the percentage of gas detected by the sensor hits the limit.@@@@1@37@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1244@LMC@2019-06-14
30005046@@@@@@The battery contact is used to place the batteries needed to provide power to the device.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1245@LMC@2019-06-14
30005047@@@@@@The components can be mounted onto a circuit board, which is covered with a plastic housing once it is completed.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1246@LMC@2019-06-14
30005048@@@@@@Through this implementation, the chances of fire accidents will be greatly reduced.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1247@LMC@2019-06-14
30005049@@@@@@The safety of the environment will be secured and there won’t be any damage cost to fork out when fire accidents are reduced.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1248@LMC@2019-06-14
30005050@@@@@@Components and assembly cost: S$ 38.00@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1249@LMC@2019-06-14
30005051@@@@@@Product Cost: S$32.50@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1250@LMC@2019-06-14
30005052@@@@@@To sum it up, this innovation will reduce fire hazards caused by stoves in households.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1251@LMC@2019-06-14
30005053@@@@@@The implementation used in this innovation involves mainly a sensor and a circuit board.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1252@LMC@2019-06-14
30005054@@@@@@The sensor is used to detect the amount of CO emitted by the gas stove.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1253@LMC@2019-06-14
30005055@@@@@@If by any chance the amount of gas detected goes beyond the limit, the sensor will activate a buzzer that will notify the user that gas is leaking.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1254@LMC@2019-06-14
30005056@@@@@@Thus preventing fire hazards.@@@@1@4@ntucle-docid:175; ntucle-sid:1255@LMC@2019-06-14
30005057@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1537@LMC@2019-06-14
30005058@@@@@@One of the most important resources known to mankind is water.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1538@LMC@2019-06-14
30005059@@@@@@The percentage of the water that cannot be consumed is approximately 96.5% while the remaining 3.5% exists as fresh water (USGS, 2015).@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1539@LMC@2019-06-14
30005060@@@@@@However, 69% of this amount is inaccessible for drinking as it is stuck within polar ice caps and glaciers.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1540@LMC@2019-06-14
30005061@@@@@@Therefore, the actual amount of fresh water that is usable is less than 1% of the entire amount of water found on Earth (McMichael, 2014).@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1541@LMC@2019-06-14
30005062@@@@@@Up to 60% of the human body is made up of water (McMichael, 2014).@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1542@LMC@2019-06-14
30005063@@@@@@Vital organs within the human body are largely made up of water.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1543@LMC@2019-06-14
30005064@@@@@@Drinking water is of utmost importance as it helps to remove body waste, lubricate joints, and helps to deliver oxygen to various body parts.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1544@LMC@2019-06-14
30005065@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:181; ntucle-sid:1545@LMC@2019-06-14
