30005264@@@@@@Background:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1270@LMC@2019-06-14
30005265@@@@@@Vehicle theft is a prevalent problem worldwide, with vehicles stolen being sold as a whole or for their parts.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1271@LMC@2019-06-14
30005266@@@@@@In Singapore, “statistics compiled for the first time by the General Insurance Association (GIA) showed that there were 341 vehicle thefts” in 2014 [1].@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1272@LMC@2019-06-14
30005267@@@@@@In Malaysia, 13407 cars were stolen in the same year.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1273@LMC@2019-06-14
30005268@@@@@@[2].@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1274@LMC@2019-06-14
30005269@@@@@@Vehicle theft causes great distress to owners, thus emphasizing the need to harness new technology in vehicle alarm systems to bring down vehicle theft rates.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1275@LMC@2019-06-14
30005270@@@@@@Problem:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1276@LMC@2019-06-14
30005271@@@@@@Most factory-fitted alarms have remained unchanged for years, functioning by the activation of loud sounds and flashing lights when the vehicle’s doors or windows are tampered with.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1277@LMC@2019-06-14
30005272@@@@@@Vehicle alarms sound similar, thus making it difficult for owners to distinguish his vehicle’s alarm from other vehicles.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1278@LMC@2019-06-14
30005273@@@@@@Thieves, armed with new technology, are easily able to deactivate these alarm systems.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1279@LMC@2019-06-14
30005274@@@@@@These factors render current alarm systems ineffective in deterring thieves.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1280@LMC@2019-06-14
30005275@@@@@@Solution:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1281@LMC@2019-06-14
30005276@@@@@@The EVAS (Enhanced Vehicle Alarm System) combines the use of the traditional alarm system with GPS trackers, immobilizers and network (4G) connectivity.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1282@LMC@2019-06-14
30005277@@@@@@These components will work together with the traditional alarm system, allowing the owner to check the status and location of his vehicle through an application in his smartphone.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1283@LMC@2019-06-14
30005278@@@@@@This app will display the doors or windows which were tampered with, allowing the owner to re-secure or lock the stated door or window.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1284@LMC@2019-06-14
30005279@@@@@@The app will also provide a button to alert the area’s police force of the vehicle’s status and location when the alarm is triggered.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1285@LMC@2019-06-14
30005280@@@@@@It can also immobilize his vehicle’s electrical systems when needed, cutting power to the engine.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1286@LMC@2019-06-14
30005281@@@@@@Benefits:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1287@LMC@2019-06-14
30005282@@@@@@With EVAS, the owner will have a multi-pronged response to a theft situation.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1288@LMC@2019-06-14
30005283@@@@@@EVAS improves the functionality of vehicle alarm systems using real-time notifications on the owner’s smartphone, improving response time by the vehicle owner and local authorities.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1289@LMC@2019-06-14
30005284@@@@@@The GPS trackers provide location updates of the vehicle, while the immobilizer can render the vehicle immobile at the owner’s will.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1290@LMC@2019-06-14
30005285@@@@@@With 4G connectivity, the alarm system can be activated at any range, unlike current alarm systems that work within radio signal range.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1291@LMC@2019-06-14
30005286@@@@@@Implementation:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:187; ntucle-sid:1292@LMC@2019-06-14
